headline.main: OUR AIRMEN BAG 20 PLANES AT LAE; 11 P-38s Shoot Down 9 Zeros Without Loss -- 11 Planes Destroyed on Ground THEN BOMBS SMASH BASE Fighting Flares Again at Sanananda -- MacArthur Looks to Early Papua Clean-Up

lead_paragraph: AT UNITED NATIONS HEADQUARTERS, Australia, Friday, Jan. 1 -- The New Year's Day communique of General Douglas MacArthur announced that twenty Japanese planes were destroyed at Lae, enemy-held base above Buna on the New Guinea north coast.
abstract: raid Buka airdrome, Solomons, and Madang and Wewak, New Guinea
